'''I'm Glad I Can Make You Cry''' is a [[World War I]] song written and composed by Chas. R. McCarron & Carey Morgan. The song was published in 1918 by Jos. W. Stern & Co. in [[New York, NY]]. The sheet music cover, illustrated by Starmer, depicts photos of [[Alice Joyce]] & Evart Overton, as well as Bessie Hamilton and Gus Hall's Minstrels.<ref>{{cite book |last=Parker |first=Bernard S. |year=2007 |title=World War I Sheet Music 1. |location=Jefferson |publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc. |page=283 |isbn=978-0-7864-2798-7 |oclc=71790113}}</ref>
The sheet music can be found at the [[Pritzker Military Museum & Library]].<ref>McCarron, Chas. R., Carey Morgan, and Starmer. 1918. ''I'm glad I can make you cry''. New York (102-104 W. 38th St.): Jos. W. Stern & Co. {{OCLC|40849869}}</ref>
